 9x9 Sudoku Generator

 
Overview - by Kemiel Dewnath

A 9x9 Sudoku puzzle generator built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Generates puzzles with valid solutions and allows toggling the solution.

Includes decorative side images for a polished look.

Fully functional in a web browser.

Features

Randomly generates playable 9x9 Sudoku puzzles.

Show/Hide Solution button to reveal or hide the solution.

Side PNG images appear on the left and right of the table for decoration.

Semi-transparent table background keeps numbers readable.

Responsive design works on desktop and mobile screens.

File Structure

index.html — main HTML page with table, buttons, and layout.

style.css — styles for the table, buttons, and side images.

sudoku.js — JavaScript logic for generating puzzles and solutions.

images/ — folder containing the decorative PNG image(s).

How It Works

HTML sets up the table, side images, and buttons.

CSS positions the table in the center with side images on the left and right.

JavaScript uses a backtracking algorithm to generate a valid Sudoku solution.

Some numbers are removed randomly to create a playable puzzle.

Buttons allow generating a new puzzle or toggling the solution.

How to Run

Open the project folder in Finder (Mac) or Explorer (Windows).

Double-click index.html to open it in a web browser.

Click "Generate New Sudoku" to create a new puzzle.

Click "Show Solution" to reveal or hide the solution.

For live editing, open in VSCode with the Live Server extension.

Customization

Replace the side PNG images with any image of your choice.

Adjust image opacity or size through CSS for visual preference.

Table background is semi-transparent to make numbers readable over decorations.

Notes

Designed for educational and casual puzzle use.

Works fully offline in a browser.

Responsive layout ensures usability on different screen sizes.